body:
expected:
install and log into owncloud, it functions as usual

what happens:
i install owncloud 5.0.0 on a new windows 2008r2 server, i install sq server 2008 r2, and it all set up correctly. then i log in, look at the files home directory. no problem.  then i log out, and instead of the login page, a blank page is loaded.  and then, no browser can get to the web server at all, from anywhere, including on the server.  essentially 5.0.0 locks up and doesn't work.

steps to reproduce:
install new 2008 r2 and patch it
install sql server 2008 r2
use the web installer to install php 5.4, php sql server drivers for 5.4, php manager
set permissions on files, set php max_upload and upload_max to 2gb and 2.2 gb, then set up request filtering (>30mb) and make sure php verbs are enabled
log in and setup owncloud
see you are on the admin page, then everything goes blank

